{"id": "stats-bags-int-guideline", "grade": 12, "steps": [{"hint": "Remember, percent means out of 100.", "type": "formula", "teach": "To find a percentage of a value, multiply the value by the percentage divided by 100.", "answer": "$10\% \text{ of } 80 = \frac{10}{100} \times 80$", "prompt": "Which formula calculates 10% of the average learner's mass?", "options": ["$10\% \text{ of } 80 = \frac{10}{100} \times 80$", "$10\% \text{ of } 80 = 10 \times 80$", "$10\% \text{ of } 80 = 80 \div 10$"], "expression": null, "step_number": 1, "final_expression": "$10\% \text{ of } 80 = \frac{10}{100} \times 80$"}, {"hint": "$\frac{10}{100} \times 80 = 8$", "type": "value", "teach": "10% of 80 is $\frac{10}{100} \times 80 = 8$ kg.", "answer": "8 \text{ kg}", "prompt": "What is 10% of 80 kg?", "options": ["8 \text{ kg}", "10,68 \text{ kg}", "80 \text{ kg}"], "expression": "$10\% \text{ of } 80 = [ ? ]$", "step_number": 2, "final_expression": "$10\% \text{ of } 80 = 8 \text{ kg}$"}, {"hint": "Is $10,68$ greater than 8?", "type": "step-fill", "teach": "If $10,68 > 8$, the average bag mass exceeds the guideline.", "answer": ">", "prompt": "Compare the estimated mean bag mass ($10,68$ kg) to the guideline (8 kg). Which comparison is correct?", "options": [">", "<", "="], "expression": "$10,68 \text{ kg} [ ? ] 8 \text{ kg}$", "step_number": 3, "final_expression": "$10,68 \text{ kg} > 8 \text{ kg}$"}, {"hint": "Compute $\frac{10,68 \times 100}{80}$.", "type": "step-fill", "teach": "Divide 10,68 by 80, then multiply by 100: $\frac{10,68}{80} \times 100 = 13,35\%$.", "answer": "13,35", "prompt": "Calculate the percentage of the estimated mean bag mass relative to average body mass. Fill in the blank: $\frac{10,68 \times 100}{80} = [ ? ]\%$", "options": ["13,35", "8", "10"], "expression": "$\frac{10,68 \times 100}{80} = [ ? ]\%$", "step_number": 4, "final_expression": "$\frac{10,68 \times 100}{80} = 13,35\%$"}, {"hint": "Is 13,35% greater than 10%?", "type": "value", "teach": "Since 13,35% > 10%, bags are heavier than the guideline allows.", "answer": "No, it is above the guideline.", "prompt": "Is the average school bag mass within the international guideline?", "options": ["No, it is above the guideline.", "Yes, it is below the guideline.", "Yes, it is exactly at the guideline."], "expression": "Mean bag mass = 13,35\% \text{ of learner mass} [ ? ] 10\%", "step_number": 5, "final_expression": "13,35\% > 10\% \newline \text{Therefore, learners' bags are heavier than the stipulated international guideline.}"}], "topic": "Statistics - Interpreting Mean & Guidelines", "question": "The mean mass of this group of learners was found to be 80 kg. On average, are these school bags satisfying the international guideline with regard to mass? Motivate your answer.

